==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Firestone
<hw>Fire"stone`</hw> <pr>(?; 110)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[AS.
<ets>f⟦ymac⟧rst⟦amac⟧n</ets> flint; <ets>f⟦ymac⟧r</ets> fire +
<ets>st⟦amac⟧n</ets> stone.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Iron pyrites,
formerly used for striking fire; also, a flint.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A stone which will bear the heat of a furnace
without injury; -- especially applied to the sandstone at the top of the
upper greensand in the south of England, used for lining kilns and
furnaces.</def> <rj><au>Ure.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Firetail</ent>⟦br⟧
